The paper deals with transceiver design strategies for the multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) interfering broadcast channel, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses interference alignment techniques, which are commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI) and communication systems (cs.COM). Finally, the paper focuses on the two-cell scenario, which is a specific case of multi-cell MIMO systems, and thus could be relevant to the subfield of multi-user MIMO (cs.MM).
